1. Save the ubuntu images to a tar/zip archive and then extract the layers and metadata files from them.(Tip: use `docker save -o` command)

(venv) evgenia@evgenia-Mi-Laptop-Pro-15:~/PycharmProjects/HW_advanced$ docker save -o ubuntu.tar ubuntu:20.04
(venv) evgenia@evgenia-Mi-Laptop-Pro-15:~/PycharmProjects/HW_advanced$ /home/evgenia/PycharmProjects/HW_advanced/ubuntu.tar
bash: /home/evgenia/PycharmProjects/HW_advanced/ubuntu.tar: Permission denied


2*. Run a container that outputs the current date and time in Rome. Should be only Dockerfile.(Tip: user 'tzdata' library)

(venv) evgenia@evgenia-Mi-Laptop-Pro-15:~/PycharmProjects/HW_advanced$ time

real    0m0,000s
user    0m0,000s
sys     0m0,000s
(venv) evgenia@evgenia-Mi-Laptop-Pro-15:~/PycharmProjects/HW_advanced$ date
п'ятниця, 28 травня 2021 22:14:40 +0300
